{"parse":{"title":"The Big Necessity","pageid":37640860,"revid":735188031,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox vcard\" style=\"width:22em\"><caption style=\"font-style:italic;padding-bottom:0.2em;\">The Big Necessity: The Unmentionable World of Human Waste and Why It Matters <span class=\"Z3988\" title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Big+Necessity%3A+The+Unmentionable+World+of+Human+Waste+and+Why+It+Matters&amp;rft.author=Rose+George\"></span></caption><tbody><tr><td colspan=\"2\" style=\"text-align:center;display:none\"></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Author</th><td>\nRose George</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Subject</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Sanitation\" title=\"Sanitation\">Sanitation</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Hygiene\" title=\"Hygiene\">Hygiene</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Genre</th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Non-fiction_literature\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Non-fiction literature\">Non-fiction</a></td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\">Published</th><td>\n2009 (Macmillan)</td></tr><tr><th scope=\"row\"><a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a></th><td>\n<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780805090833\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780805090833\">9780805090833</a></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><i><b>The Big Necessity: The Unmentionable World of Human Waste and Why It Matters</b></i> (published in the United Kingdom as <i>The Big Necessity: Adventures in the World of Human Waste</i>), written by <a href=\"/wiki/Rose_George\" title=\"Rose George\">Rose George</a>, is a descriptive representation of the history, advancement, cultural variation, solutions, and international need of <a href=\"/wiki/Sanitation\" title=\"Sanitation\">sanitation</a>. This work, written for the purpose of global awareness of sanitation, highlights the current state of a global crisis. George gives insight into how sanitation around the world depicts the standard of living in that area. George uses her own personal experiences as examples to explain the sanitary conditions of areas around the world.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  Worldwide, 2.6 billion people (40% of the world's population) do not have sanitary facilities or systems to dispose of waste.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Studies show that 95% of human waste is released into lakes, rivers, and ponds in <a href=\"/wiki/Developing_countries\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Developing countries\">developing countries</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Williams_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Williams-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>  George discusses the lack of sanitation and toilets for the majority of the world and the resultant infection of water supplies causing 10% of the world\u2019s communicable diseases.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The Big Necessity is an informative book that brings to light the different ways people around the world dispose of their excrement. This book brings to light certain facts such as that access to a toilet adds 20 years to the average life.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=The_Big_Necessity&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"referen